Payments are the real bottleneck for agentic AI.

As AI agents move from answering questions to executing actions, traditional human-centric payment rails break down. Credit cards, manual approvals, and opaque billing don‚Äôt scale for autonomous systems.

Coinbase‚Äôs x402 is a big unlock. Making payments native to HTTP enables true pay-per-call APIs with machine-readable authorization, built-in auditability, and clean reconciliation.

This is why Kite‚Äôs roadmap stands out.

Kite is clearly positioning itself as core infrastructure for autonomous economies, built around six pillars:
‚Ä¢ Agentic Trust
‚Ä¢ Agentic Settlement
‚Ä¢ SmartDev Infra
‚Ä¢ Agent Network Operations
‚Ä¢ AgenticFi
‚Ä¢ Agentic Ecosystem Growth

With native x402 compatibility, Kite becomes an execution and settlement layer where agents can transact securely, autonomously, and at scale.

The shift is clear:
Agent identity, permissioned execution, and programmable settlement are no longer optional. They‚Äôre foundational.
